<dl id="n17108b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n17" href="#n17108b">N17 (VI.B.9)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n17all.htm#n17108b"> 108(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> balaaming / <font face="wake">X</font> <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n17108b"><li>FW 566.09 </li><li><a href="../../flex/s/lexs.htm#n17108b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/s/l39s.htm#n17108b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n17108b">MS BL 47485-11</ms> </li><li>JJA 60:295 <a name="sd2y" href="../../FF/fdra/sda.htm#sd2y">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/s/sd2.htm#n17108b">Draft: III&sect;4.2</a>+ </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: An angel is visible only to the donkey the [Biblical] prophet Balaam is riding, and the donkey tries to avoid it. Balaam beats the animal for refusing to move, whereupon the donkey is miraculously given the power of speech and upbraids Balaam for his treatment (Numbers 22:28). </mm> </dd></dl>
